st v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2 and above, so `net462` is fine\n\nThe unified `MSTest` package replaces the old separate packages (`MSTest.TestFramework`, `MSTest.TestAdapter`, and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`), though the namespace `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` remains for backward compatibility. I should also check for any breaking changes in the test code itself, particularly around attributes like `[Timeout]` which had behavior changes in v3.\n\nFor the project file, I need to remove the old assembly reference and the `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` package, then add the single `MSTest` package — I'll go with a stable recent version like 3.7.0 or 3.8.0.\n\nThe test class itself should work without changes since the `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace is still available in the newer MSTest package.","outputTokens":1365,"requestId":"241D:34D8DE:41C24A:4699CE:6A031074"},"id":"2276a190-f1e9-40f0-b0c6-ed8265526734","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:35:42.565Z","parentId":"3a8a3232-42cb-4dc6-bf53-6e7cebbb4711"}
